results.deck: Verdier is a Paris Master of the Night, who gave himself to the Great Old Ones
results.description: Verdier is a Master of the Night who lived in Paris. Humans weren't enough for him, he wanted to control all the Masters of the Night. He met Tenardier, an architect and alchemist member of the cult of the Great Old Ones, who offered him greater power in exchange of immortality as one of his un-deads. Tenardier and his followers were about the fulfill a ritual that was supposed to turn Verdier in a superior being, but Araxe De Kerkadio intervened to stop it and threw Verdier into the sacrificial pit. That caused a great explosion to occur, sign of the rage of the ancient gods. She thought that was the end, but it was still alive. Tenardier brought him to one of his manors, where Verdier recovered his strength, but, the Great Old Ones turned him into a mindless and horrible monster. With time, Verdier expanded himself in the entire mansion, becoming one with it, and started to consume the people who set up home there, turning them into his slaves.
results.name: Verdier

results.deck: Cybernetic super-brain created by Everett Ducklair.
results.description:
Uno was created by Everett Ducklair and guards the Ducklair Tower after he left. He quickly befriends the Duck Avenger alias Donald Duck when he moved to the tower and becomes his ally and advisor against threats like the Time Pirate or the Evronians

He is love with the reporter Lyla Lay, after discovering that she's an android working for the time police.

At some point, it's revealed that he has an evil back-up system called Dos

Odin Eidolon, a time traveller from the future, is eventually revealed to be the future incarnation of Uno.
results.name: Uno

results.deck: Sho-Huan is an enigmatic man with the ability to freely travel in the multiverse.
results.description: When Maître Abel was killed by an alternative Araxe De Kerkadio in a parallel France, he was unable to flee in another world, but instead sent his mind, memories and personality to another version of himself. John Ross, a travelling magician of the Victorian London, inherited those gifts and his powers. Initially, he didn't comprehend what happened and was unable to control his powers, wandering randomly through parallel worlds of different ages or structure, as well as different flows of time. Eventually he realized everything and mastered his powers, sending his mind to another self each time he was on the verge of death. He lived uncountably lives, in many worlds and eras, so much that he even lost the count. During one of these trips he found the Plateau of Leng, the followers of the Kuen - Yuin and the cult of the Great Old Ones. From that day, he dedicated his life to bringing them back, becoming one the most elusive and dangerous enemies of Harlan Draka.
results.name: Sho-Huan
